venue.description: The Cuypers Library is the largest and oldest art historical library in the Netherlands. Following an intensive restoration campaign, it has now been fully returned to its former glory. The public will finally be able to admire the 19th century library’s splendid reading room.

items.text: it's amazing. tip: if you just want to admire the library and take some pictures, enter from the 2nd floor, not the 1st. there are people working on the 1st and taking pictures is forbidden
Please please please be quite when you enter here. People use it as an actual library and they work at the ground floor. The library room itself is gorgeous, you shouldn't miss this!
Free eduroam in the library FTW!
It smells like old books and wisdom in here! Love it!
You can enter the library both downstairs and upstairs.
